%N A394914 a(n) is the number of faces with the highest number of sides in Johnson solid J_n.
%H A394914 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Johnson_solids">List of Johnson solids</a>.
%F A394914 a(n) = A394912(n, A394913(n)).
%e A394914 a(32) = 7 because Johnson solid J_32 (pentagonal orthocupolarotunda) has 15 triangular faces, 5 square faces and 7 pentagonal faces.
%t A394914 A394914[n_] := Count[#, Max[#]] & [Map[Length, PolyhedronData["J" <> ToString[n], "FaceIndices"]]];
%t A394914 Array[A394914, 92] (* Gives the full sequence *)
